<span id="freeTextContainer502052060444136206"><b>4 ★</b><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/41209.Jennifer_Haigh' title='Jennifer Haigh' rel='nofollow noopener'>Jennifer Haigh</a> was unknown to me when I started reading <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9592213.Faith' title='Faith by Jennifer Haigh' rel='nofollow noopener'>Faith</a>. Once I began I could not stop (oh that flood of reader’s oxytocin when you discover a new author with a body of work to look forward to). Five years on GR and I have not seen (or noted) her books being read and reviewed. <br/><br/>Father Art is a Catholic priest accused of child molestation. Sheila is his half sister and our narrator <b>“My penance is to tell this ragged truth as completely as I know it,” she says, “fully aware that it is much</b></span>
  <span id="freeText502052060444136206" style="display:none"><b>4 ★</b><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/41209.Jennifer_Haigh" title="Jennifer Haigh" rel="nofollow noopener">Jennifer Haigh</a> was unknown to me when I started reading <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9592213.Faith" title="Faith by Jennifer Haigh" rel="nofollow noopener">Faith</a>. Once I began I could not stop (oh that flood of reader’s oxytocin when you discover a new author with a body of work to look forward to). Five years on GR and I have not seen (or noted) her books being read and reviewed. <br /><br />Father Art is a Catholic priest accused of child molestation. Sheila is his half sister and our narrator <b>“My penance is to tell this ragged truth as completely as I know it,” she says, “fully aware that it is much too little, much too late.”</b> She is estranged from her family and her faith, her doubts with both adding to the building mystery and suspense.<br />The layered pages start to peel away like an onion as the backstory and history of the fractured Breem/McGann family comes to light. I was back in the dark confessional overhearing the sins of someone on the other side attempting reconciliation, <i>Bless me Father for I have sinned</i>.<br />Her writing has been described as nuanced, gripping, and totally immersive and I enthusiastically proclaim my Amens!</span>
