    <a title="Betsy Robinson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5149179-betsy-robinson"><img alt="Betsy Robinson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1404493492p2/5149179.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2627235725?book_show_action=true">Dec 31, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Betsy Robinson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Betsy Robinson" href="/user/show/5149179-betsy-robinson">Betsy Robinson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780062065209" href="/book/show/9592214-faith">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2627235725" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16489022536484722877">This is a sturdily written saga about an Irish Catholic family in Boston and a priest sex abuse case. I enjoyed it, was interested in the plot and how it all turned out, but I was not engaged emotionally. The story is well reported by the sister of a priest accused of molestation. Characters are well described, feelings are described—it is a well-written report that may have more of an emotional appeal for Catholics than it did for me. Also, it is the odd novel that I think might work much bette</span>
  <span id="freeText16489022536484722877" style="display:none">This is a sturdily written saga about an Irish Catholic family in Boston and a priest sex abuse case. I enjoyed it, was interested in the plot and how it all turned out, but I was not engaged emotionally. The story is well reported by the sister of a priest accused of molestation. Characters are well described, feelings are described—it is a well-written report that may have more of an emotional appeal for Catholics than it did for me. Also, it is the odd novel that I think might work much better as movie, with actors to embody feeling that is largely missing here.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16489022536484722877" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


